properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 5 at 9:56PM MST until January 7 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HIGH WINDS EXPECTED TO REDEVELOP LATE TONIGHT THROUGH
TUESDAY...

* WHAT...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 75 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County,
North Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range, South
Laramie Range Foothills and Central Laramie County Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 8 AM MST Tuesday.

* TIMING...Until 7 AM MST Sunday.

* WINDS...West 40 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 70 MPH.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL IMPACTS...Blowing snow will be an issue near the
mountains, reducing visibilities around one half mile with
gusts over 65 MPH possible.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST TUESDAY
